adjectives.description: insulated (comparative more insulated, superlative most insulated)

entries.meaning: Protected from heat, cold, noise etc, by being surrounded with an insulating material.
(of an electrically conducting material) Isolated or separated from other conducting materials, or sources of electricity.
examples: Early insulated wires were covered in silk rather than plastic.

entries.meaning: (astronomy, dated) Situated at so great a distance as to be beyond the effect of gravitation; said of stars supposed to be so far apart that the effect of their mutual attraction is undetectable[1802].
simple past tense and past participle of insulate
